Package station

Class SlotCreator

  • java.lang.Object
    • station.SlotCreator
  • public class SlotCreator
extends java.lang.Object
    Factory class used exclusively to create slots for each station according to parameters that may change, namely minimal percentage of occupied slots and minimal percentage of electric bikes. In case of creation of a new bike type, this class needs to be modified with the correct percentage of presence in the stations. For now, the information concerning minimal occupation rate and minimal electric bike rate is stored in the attributes percentage_empty and percentage_regular, because they represent the complement of these information, that is, the maximal percentage of empty slots and regular bikes.

    • Method Detail

      • fillSlots

        public ParkingSlot[] fillSlots​(int stationId,
                               int number_of_slots)
        Method for adequately filling the slots of a newly creation station. It is the only method that should be used by this class, and represents the factory creation method.
        Parameters:
        stationId - ID number of the station whose slots are being filled
        number_of_slots - number of slots to be filled
        Returns:
        a ParkingSlot array containing all slots correctly initialized and respecting the constraints for each station concerning minimal occupation and bike type rates.
